		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.94]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=fhrugby&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>It might be my imagination, but I notice slightly less evade failures when my agilty is buffed by a high lvl shaman, or it might be better to say,I notice slightly more evade failures after my high lvl shammy agility buff fades. =). Even with that said, it will fail often, and if you are getting hit hard and have more than 30% of your hp, back off out of range, and the mob will go back to tank, wait 2 or 3 ticks or so and try evade again each time. You might want to use evade every chance it is available, not just when mobs hit you, if you are not doing that already, as it will lower u on hate list so you avoid getting aggro at all.<br><br>If you want to avoid too many misses get your attack and other melee skills up, have heard some say dex also increases chance of hit, if this is so, I recommend the jagged blade of morning in offhand in lieu of blood pt b/c of the dex bonus, 1HS skill learning and better ratio then bloodpoint and plus blood pt does not proc till lvl 50 and when it does it sucks as a proc on a rogue used weapon, lots of aggro for very little hp gained. If your main can afford it I recommend buying or even better making a set of haze panther gear for this toon as the stat bonuses on the gear are awsome for a rogue including stamina, str, agi and dex. Though it will have less ac than other gear so pratice those skills on avoiding aggro inclding starting a 30 secs or so after the tank and hitting evade every chance and no proc on weapons.<br>Finally u can get u bs up higher by increasing your str and you BS skill, BS is the only skill (besides poison to save $$) I recommend training at guild trainer as a rogue b/c it always seems to lag behind the other combat skills.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jul 16 10:34:24 2003</em></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Baron McSean Shadowraider level 59 Halfling Rogue,<br>Cullum Level 36 Dwarf Paladin<br>Leapof Faith 24 Froglok Cleric<br>Necrosaurous Level 23 Iksar Necromancer<br>Xauvian Level 1 Trader Mule Extraordinaire<br>XEGONY SERVER</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mlr>
