		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=61546"><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>1262 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.67]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Since evade is basically hiding during combat anything that breaks hide can cause evade to fail.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you get knocked back by an attack within 3 sec of evade it will fail.  If you get hit by a DOT spell it will fail if the DOT pulsed within 3 sec prior to your evade attempt (a pulse is 6 seconds)  Evade can fail if the mob can see through your Hide normally. It can fail due to plain old bad luck.<br><br>The chance of success is higher if the mob is facing away from you.  So, evade before the mob turns and aggro's you.  It works better.  I typically evade whenever it becomes available. That way I keep moving down the aggro list and never draw aggro (unless the tank is really that bad at taunting). Works great on Black Reavers.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
